<h2>Alabama Incentives & Rebates</h2>
<p>Alabama offers several valuable incentives for solar panel and HVAC installations that significantly improve the financial benefits of these energy-efficient upgrades:</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Federal Solar Tax Credit (30%):</strong> The federal government provides a 30% tax credit for solar panel installations through 2032, then stepping down to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. This credit applies to the full cost of the solar system, including equipment, installation, and permitting. For a typical \$25,000 solar installation, this credit provides \$7,500 in tax savings. The credit can be carried forward to future tax years if it exceeds current tax liability.</li>

<li><strong>Alabama Property Tax Exemption:</strong> Alabama Code Section 40-9-27 provides a complete exemption from property taxes for solar energy systems installed on residential properties. This exemption means that while solar panels may increase your home's value, they won't increase your annual property tax burden, providing ongoing savings throughout the system's lifetime.</li>

<li><strong>Alabama Power Solar Programs:</strong> Alabama Power offers net metering for residential solar customers, allowing homeowners to receive credit for excess electricity produced by their solar systems. The utility also provides interconnection services and has streamlined processes for solar installations under 20kW capacity.</li>

<li><strong>TVA Green Power Providers Program:</strong> For customers in the Tennessee Valley Authority service area (northern Alabama), the Green Power Providers program offers additional benefits for renewable energy installations, including simplified interconnection and renewable energy credits.</li>

<li><strong>HVAC Rebates and Incentives:</strong> Alabama Power and other utilities throughout the state offer rebates for high-efficiency HVAC equipment, including heat pumps, smart thermostats, and duct sealing services. These rebates typically range from \$300-800 for qualifying equipment installations.</li>
</ul>

